The received power can be found using the Friis transmission formula. For half-wave dipoles aligned and with the path normal to each, the gain is 1.64 (linear).  
With \(P_t = 1000\,\text{W}\), \(R = 500\,\text{km}\), \(f = 200\,\text{MHz}\) (\(\lambda = 1.5\,\text{m}\)), the received power is approximately \(1.53 \times 10^{-10}\,\text{W}\).  

